name: CloudFrontDistributionConfigOrigin
description: Origin is a property of the DistributionConfig property that describes an Amazon CloudFront distribution origin.

properties.name: CustomOriginConfig
properties.desc: Origin information to specify a custom origin.

properties.name: DomainName
properties.desc: The DNS name of the Amazon Simple Storage Service (S3) bucket or the HTTP server from which you want CloudFront to get objects for this origin.

properties.name: Id
properties.desc: An identifier for the origin. The value of Id must be unique within the distribution.

properties.name: OriginPath
properties.desc: The path that CloudFront uses to request content from an S3 bucket or custom origin. The combination of the DomainName and OriginPath properties must resolve to a valid path. The value must start with a slash mark (/) and cannot end with a slash mark.

properties.name: S3OriginConfig
properties.desc: Origin information to specify an S3 origin.
